  "chapter": {
    "number": 2,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Israel Has Forsaken God"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "Now the word of the LORD came to me, saying,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          "“Go and proclaim in the hearing of Jerusalem that this is what the LORD says:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "‘I remember the devotion of your youth,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "your love as a bride,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "how you followed Me in the wilderness,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in a land not sown.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Israel was holy to the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the firstfruits of His harvest.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "All who devoured her",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "found themselves guilty;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "disaster came upon them,’”",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "declares the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          "Hear the word of the LORD, O house of Jacob, and all you families of the house of Israel."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          "This is what the LORD says:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“What fault did your fathers find in Me",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "that they strayed so far from Me,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and followed worthless idols,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and became worthless themselves?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They did not ask, ‘Where is the LORD",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who brought us up from the land of Egypt,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who led us through the wilderness,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "through a land of deserts and pits,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "a land of drought and darkness,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a land where no one travels and no one lives?’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I brought you into a fertile land",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to eat its fruit and bounty,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "but you came and defiled My land,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and made My inheritance detestable.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The priests did not ask,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "‘Where is the LORD?’",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The experts in the law no longer knew Me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the leaders rebelled against Me.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The prophets prophesied by Baal",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and followed useless idols.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore, I will contend with you again,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "declares the LORD,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and I will bring a case",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "against your children’s children.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cross over to the coasts of Cyprus",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2854
          },
          {
            "text": "and take a look;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "send to Kedar and consider carefully;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "see if there has ever been anything like this:",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Has a nation ever changed its gods,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "though they are no gods at all?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Yet My people have exchanged their Glory",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2855
          },
          {
            "text": "for useless idols.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Be stunned by this, O heavens;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "be shocked and utterly appalled,”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "declares the LORD."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“For My people have committed two evils:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "They have forsaken Me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the fountain of living water,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and they have dug their own cisterns—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "broken cisterns that cannot hold water.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Consequence of Israel’s Sin"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Is Israel a slave?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Was he born into slavery?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Why then has he become prey?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The young lions have roared at him;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they have growled with a loud voice.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They have laid waste his land;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "his cities lie in ruins, without inhabitant.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The men of Memphis",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2856
          },
          {
            "text": "and Tahpanhes",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "have shaved the crown of your head.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Have you not brought this on yourself",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "by forsaking the LORD your God",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "when He led you in the way?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Now what will you gain on your way to Egypt",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to drink the waters of the Nile",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2857
          },
          {
            "text": "?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "What will you gain on your way to Assyria",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to drink the waters of the Euphrates",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2858
          },
          {
            "text": "?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Your own evil will discipline you;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "your own apostasies will reprimand you.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Consider and realize",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "how evil and bitter it is",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for you to forsake the LORD your God",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and to have no fear of Me,”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "declares the Lord GOD of Hosts."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“For long ago you broke your yoke",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and tore off your chains,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "saying, ‘I will not serve!’",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Indeed, on every high hill",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and under every green tree",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "you lay down as a prostitute.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I had planted you like a choice vine",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from the very best seed.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "How could you turn yourself before Me",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "into a rotten, wild vine?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Although you wash with lye",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and use an abundance of soap,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the stain of your guilt",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "is still before Me,”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "declares the Lord GOD."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Israel’s Unfaithfulness"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“How can you say, ‘I am not defiled;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I have not run after the Baals’?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Look at your behavior in the valley;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "acknowledge what you have done.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "You are a swift young she-camel",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "galloping here and there,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "a wild donkey at home in the wilderness,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "sniffing the wind in the heat of her desire.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Who can restrain her passion?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "All who seek her need not weary themselves;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in mating season they will find her.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You should have kept your feet from going bare",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and your throat from being thirsty.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "But you said, ‘It is hopeless!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "For I love foreign gods,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and I must go after them.’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "As the thief is ashamed when he is caught,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so the house of Israel is disgraced.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They, their kings, their officials,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "their priests, and their prophets",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "say to a tree, ‘You are my father,’",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and to a stone, ‘You gave me birth.’",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For they have turned their backs to Me",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and not their faces,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "yet in the time of trouble they beg,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "‘Rise up and save us!’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 28,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But where are the gods you made for yourselves?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Let them rise up in your time of trouble",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and save you if they can;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for your gods are as numerous",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "as your cities, O Judah.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 29,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Why do you bring a case against Me?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "You have all rebelled against Me,”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "declares the LORD."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 30,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“I have struck your sons in vain;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they accepted no discipline.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Your own sword has devoured your prophets",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like a voracious lion.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 31,
        "content": [
          "You people of this generation, consider the word of the LORD:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Have I been a wilderness to Israel",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or a land of dense darkness?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Why do My people say,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "‘We are free to roam;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "we will come to You no more’?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 32,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Does a maiden forget her jewelry",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or a bride her wedding sash?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Yet My people have forgotten Me",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for days without number.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 33,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "How skillfully you pursue love!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Even the most immoral of women",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "could learn from your ways.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 34,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Moreover, your skirts are stained",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with the blood of the innocent poor,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "though you did not find them breaking in.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "But in spite of all these things",
            "poem": 1
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 35,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "you say, ‘I am innocent.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Surely His anger will turn from me.’",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Behold, I will judge you,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "because you say, ‘I have not sinned.’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 36,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "How unstable you are,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "constantly changing your ways!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "You will be disappointed by Egypt",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "just as you were by Assyria.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 37,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Moreover, you will leave that place",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with your hands on your head,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for the LORD has rejected those you trust;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you will not prosper by their help.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
